flowRoot.flowPara: Relations between the browser and the web server
From the HTML informations, the browser creates the DOM (Document Object Model), his own interpretation of the HTML file, that will be modified by the CSS and the javascript information.
The relations between the browser and the server are happening on a request-response mode.
The “thing” that takes the content from the database and with HTML information transforms it in a static HTML document
“What should I do with this url? What does it relate to?”
The application constructs an HTML file, from the PHP program (that already contains “abstract” HTML code) and the corresponding content in the database.
General layout information: this kind of element is here, it has that attribute (class).
Stylesheet: this class means that all elements marked as such have this and that precise characteristics.
Means an action with this and this element.
This element is here, and il should be filled with such content from the database.
“What does that CSS, JS, or image reference in the HTML relate to?”
“To this CSS, JS, or image file!”
Puts enough information in the HTML file so that then it is possible to distinguish the PHP part of the code and the database part: so that it could potentially be re-created!
